    <p><strong>The Central Question:</strong> Why do some of us have to unlearn how to learn before we can actually learn anything?</p>

    <p>For people whose nervous systems don't match the standard educational model—neurodivergent people, embodied learners, those who need to discover rather than be taught—the question "How do I learn?" becomes existential.</p>

