    <p class="rabbit-hole-question"><em>How do we move between states without needing perfect pitch?</em></p>

    <p><strong>The Central Question:</strong> What if the most solid foundations need to be the most flexible?</p>

    <p>Miles Davis: "It's the note AFTER the dissonant note that matters." Music physics: lower notes have more relativity, higher notes have less room for interpretation.</p>

